{"id":403,"date":"2019-03-01T21:09:48","date_gmt":"2019-03-01T21:09:48","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/?page_id=403"},"modified":"2019-03-06T19:41:24","modified_gmt":"2019-03-06T19:41:24","slug":"twitter-bot-future-of-colour","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/twitter-bot-future-of-colour\/","title":{"rendered":"Twitter Bot: Future of Colo(u)r"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h1>If I could have any job for a week, I&#8217;d like to be the guy who names new colours.<\/h1>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1142\" src=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02.png\" alt=\"Twitter Bot: Future of Colo(u)r is a javascript Twitter Bot I made that uses algorithms to create random colour gradients and random colour names. I was responsible for concept development and javascript development.\" class=\"wp-image-406\" srcset=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02.png 2500w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02-300x137.png 300w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02-768x351.png 768w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02-1024x468.png 1024w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-02-1568x716.png 1568w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1142\" src=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01.png\" alt=\"Twitter Bot: Future of Colo(u)r is a javascript Twitter Bot I made that uses algorithms to create random colour gradients and random colour names. I was responsible for concept development and javascript development.\" class=\"wp-image-405\" srcset=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01.png 2500w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01-300x137.png 300w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01-768x351.png 768w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01-1024x468.png 1024w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-01-1568x716.png 1568w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1142\" src=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03.png\" alt=\"Twitter Bot: Future of Colo(u)r is a javascript Twitter Bot I made that uses algorithms to create random colour gradients and random colour names. I was responsible for concept development and javascript development.\" class=\"wp-image-407\" srcset=\"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03.png 2500w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03-300x137.png 300w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03-768x351.png 768w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03-1024x468.png 1024w, https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/03\/Future-of-Colours-03-1568x716.png 1568w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>That&#8217;s why I made a Twitter bot that does just that!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\n randomly generates two fun Pantone names, and then creates a SVG \ngradient between these colours. Sometimes it&#8217;s funny. Sometimes it even \nlooks good.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And sometimes it captures the essential, ephemeral nature of fashion forecasting, just enough to be plausible.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>This is a Twitter bot I wrote in <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/galaxykate\/tracery\/tree\/tracery2\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tracery<\/a> over <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/cheapbotsdonequick.com\/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here<\/a>. Check out my source code on <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/adamhorne.com\/#\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GitHub<\/a>.<br><br>And like the most desperate social media influencers, it randomly tweets every couple of hours<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/FutureOfColor\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> @FutureOfColor<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\/\/A \ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83c\udfa8<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If I could have any job for a week, I&#8217;d like to be the guy who names new colours. That&#8217;s why I made a Twitter bot that does just that! It randomly generates two fun Pantone names, and then creates a SVG gradient between these colours. Sometimes it&#8217;s funny. Sometimes it even looks good. And [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/403"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=403"}],"version-history":[{"count":6,"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/403\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":764,"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/403\/revisions\/764"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/adamhorne.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=403"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}